  "title": "Moby Multiple Language Lists of Common Words",
  "author": "Ward, Grady",
  "summary": "This Project Gutenberg entry documents the Moby Language II package by Grady Ward, a public-domain collection of large word lists in five languages. It explains that the lists are ASCII text files for MSDOS distribution, compressed in a single zip archive and using CRLF delimiters. The documentation warns that older lists lack Unicode and 8-bit accented characters, using phonetic spellings with backslashes and other markers instead, making accurate recovery of original accented forms infeasible. File contents and counts for French, German, Italian, Japanese and Spanish are listed, with sizes, and brief extraction and quick-start instructions are provided for users worldwide.",
